Sectorlandia

November 17, 2023

Library \(\uparrow\) Nav Hub | Simulation Studies | BI Transmission

The malaria landscape of Sectorlandia is remarkably similar to the northern part of Bioko Island. In sectorlandia, we are interested in spatial targeting and tailoring at a reasonably fine spatial grain.

Sectors & Areas

We subdivide the landscape into areas and sectors:

  • There are 84 areas, each one approximately 1 km \(\times\) 1 km

  • There are 2502 sectors, each one approximately 100 m \(\times\) 100 m

Humans

Pop

Some basic information about the human populations:

  • Around \(209,100\) people live in 2500 occupied sectors (i.e. 100m \(\times\) 100m).

  • Sectorlandia is an island, and the total occupied area is approximately \(17.6\) km \(\times\) \(7.8\) km.

The population is highly unevenly distributed. These are the histograms of population density and logged population density:

We can show how the population is distributed on the map by coloring the pixels – the lighter in color, the more densely it is populated.
